Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
8:51 AM Defendant David Edward Kislenger in court.  Attorney Gabriel Andres Pollak in court for David Edward Kislenger.  Prosecuting attorney James Jay Rennicke Esq in court for the State of Wisconsin. Case is on for preliminary hearing.  State calls first witness, Detective Travis Thiex, who is sworn in and testifies.  Witness has identified the defendant.  Venue is made.  Atty Pollak crosses.  No redirect or further witnesses.  State asks for bind-over.  Atty Pollak wishes to argue.  State argues for a bind over.  Atty Pollak argues against a bind over.  Court finds probable cause that a crime has been committed and the defendant probably committed it.  The matter is bound over for further proceedings.  The State files information, notes Information will allege a "Substantial Battery" and explains.  Case proceeds to Arraignment.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of information, def. waives reading.  Court informs def. of charges, possible penalties and rights.  NG plea entered to all counts.  Defendant demands speedy trial.
Status conference scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 11:45 am.
Status conference on October 27, 2022 at 11:45 am.
Preliminary hearing on October 20, 2022 at 08:45 am.
No contact with the victim or their residence.  Maintain absolute sobriety.

2:15 PM Defendant David Edward Kislenger appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Gabriel Andres Pollak in court for David Edward Kislenger.  Attorney Kevin Thomas Schmidt in court for State of Wisconsin. Def appears from Barron County Jail.  ADA Schmidt has a conflict, will stand mute.  Case on for an Initial Appearance.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of complaint, waives reading.  Court informs Defendant of charges, possible penalties and rights.  Defendant pleads NG to misdemeanors.  Atty Pollak argues for bond modification.  ADA Schmidt stands mute.  Court addresses def.  Def unable to post any cash.  Court reduces cash bond to $250.  Same conditions.
